              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A multiwire proportional counter, with an",
                "active area of 15.0 cm x 5.0 cm, followed by a double-",
                "sided silicon strip detector were used to record the",
                "ERs.",
                "A mylar foil 0.5 um thick was used as the entrance",
                "window of the MWPC in order to minimize the ER energy",
                "loss.",
                "The effective active area of the MWPC was reduced to",
                "11.0 X 5.0 cm2, due to foil supporting flange.",
                "The MWPC was operated at ~3 mbar of isobutane."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Silicon detectors were placed at 25 degree,",
                "with respect to the beam direction in the horizontal",
                "plane, for absolute normalization of ER cross sections."
              ]
            }
